From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Artjom W. <aco.art@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 1 Apr 2026 14:46:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] u-boot: configs: add Vontar H618 defconfig

Create a dedicated Vontar H618 defconfig that keeps the required H618
board settings, but stays close to the known-good x96-mate boot
profile. Keep the legacy U-Boot LAN options, DDR3 at 648 MHz,
AXP313/r_i2c, broken-cd on mmc0 and eMMC on slot 2, while explicitly
dropping the zero2w SPI-flash / fastboot / USB gadget extras that are
not part of the working LAN baseline.

Assisted-by: Artjom W. <aco.art@gmail.com>
---
 configs/vontar_h618_zero2w_defconfig | 49 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 49 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 configs/vontar_h618_zero2w_defconfig

diff --git a/configs/vontar_h618_zero2w_defconfig b/configs/vontar_h618_zero2w_defconfig
new file mode 100644
--- /dev/null
+++ b/configs/vontar_h618_zero2w_defconfig
@@ -0,0 +1,37 @@
+CONFIG_ARM=y
+CONFIG_ARCH_SUNXI=y
+CONFIG_DEFAULT_DEVICE_TREE="allwinner/sun50i-h618-vontar-h618"
+CONFIG_SPL=y
+CONFIG_DRAM_SUNXI_DX_ODT=0x03030303
+CONFIG_DRAM_SUNXI_DX_DRI=0x0e0e0e0e
+CONFIG_DRAM_SUNXI_CA_DRI=0x1c12
+CONFIG_DRAM_SUNXI_ODT_EN=0x1
+CONFIG_DRAM_SUNXI_TPR0=0xc0000c05
+CONFIG_DRAM_SUNXI_TPR2=0x0
+CONFIG_DRAM_SUNXI_TPR10=0x2f0007
+CONFIG_DRAM_SUNXI_TPR11=0xffffdddd
+CONFIG_DRAM_SUNXI_TPR12=0xfedf7557
+CONFIG_MACH_SUN50I_H616=y
+CONFIG_SUNXI_DRAM_H616_DDR3_1333=y
+CONFIG_DRAM_CLK=648
+CONFIG_R_I2C_ENABLE=y
+CONFIG_MMC_SUNXI_SLOT_EXTRA=2
+CONFIG_MMC_BROKEN_CD=y
+CONFIG_I2C3_ENABLE=y
+CONFIG_SPL_I2C=y
+CONFIG_SPL_SYS_I2C_LEGACY=y
+CONFIG_SYS_I2C_MVTWSI=y
+CONFIG_SYS_I2C_SLAVE=0x7f
+CONFIG_SYS_I2C_SPEED=100000
+CONFIG_SYS_MONITOR_LEN=786432
+CONFIG_SUPPORT_EMMC_BOOT=y
+CONFIG_MMC_IO_VOLTAGE=y
+CONFIG_MMC_UHS_SUPPORT=y
+CONFIG_ENV_IS_IN_FAT=y
+CONFIG_PHY_REALTEK=y
+CONFIG_SUN8I_EMAC=y
+CONFIG_AXP_PMIC_BUS=y
+CONFIG_AXP313_POWER=y
+CONFIG_AXP_DCDC3_VOLT=1500
+CONFIG_USB_EHCI_HCD=y
+CONFIG_USB_OHCI_HCD=y

-- 
2.43.0
